@Toc "Main"

HISTORY
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
1.03  - Now you can change sample information
       (Name, author, Copyright and Annotations)

      - Press left or right arrow loads previous or next preset
      
      - If you delete all samples, PIP will stay in the same preset

      - Auto load preset 1 at startup

1.02a - Sound Probe sometimes generates wrong size to the header.
        PIP now loads a sample saved by Sound Probe.

1.02  - fixed major bug when starting on a NTSC Amiga

      - moved 'Status' line to top.

1.01  - fixed "stupid forgot to clear text" when loading a sample with
        shorter text lenght.

      - now you can play big stereo samples instant too.
        As you know the right channel data is stored after the left channel
        data, so if you want to play really big stereo samples it might take
        a second or two for your HD to seek at the right position. This is
        now fixed by holding down the key, wait for the status request and
        release the key. The sample will now play with NO delay what so ever.
        
      - If you press a gadget with the left mouse button, PIP now goes
        directly to the load sample request.

      - While seeking a stereo sample greater than 150 KB screen is turning 
        red.

      - Fixed bug when saving preset 6 and 7
      
1.00  - first public release.


